720217f-c.title: Manhattan: Greenwich Street - Franklin Street
720217f-c.text:
Greenwich Street, south from Franklin (In No. 1) and arren
(in No's. 2 \& 3) Streets, showing the Ninth Avennue elevated line
overhanging the Street. Prominent buildings seen in No. 1 are
the Woolworth, a loft structure at the S.E. corner of Greenwich and
Jay Streets. the ne~ cowntown Post Office and the City Bank Farmers
Trust Co. Bidg. Views 2 and 3 show mainly the recently completed
Post Office Bldg.
July 4, 1938.
Views 1,2 and 3
P. L. Sperr
NO RPRODUCTIONS
